## Root Cause

The only migration in `supabase/migrations/` is a single-line smoke test:

```sql
COMMENT ON TABLE jobs IS 'Hendren Platform - staging baseline validated';
```

This assumes the `jobs` table already exists. It does not on staging. The staging database is a
blank Postgres 17 instance with no schema applied.

The full production schema (jobs, schedule, companies, trades, cost-codes, files, etc.) was never
committed to `supabase/migrations/` as an initial migration. It exists only on the production
project (`oiyujpkqfbqmjyxefwbj`).

